(10, 1, '2016-05-16 18:48:43', '2016-05-16 22:48:43', 'With the 2016 National Collegiate Counter-Strike League (NCCSL) Division II Playoffs underway, the top teams in both conferences are battling for the Division Two champion title.\r\n\r\nPlayoffs will be conducted with a single elimination tournament bracket. For both the East and West conferences, the top four teams will compete for the title of conference champion and a spot in the East versus West National Finals. In each conference, the bracket is built by pitting the top contender against the team in fourth place, and the second and third place teams facing each other in the conference semifinals.\r\n\r\nPlayoff spots have been awarded based on a point system, with teams earning different amounts of points based on the outcomes of normal season matches. These matches were played as a series of two games against the same opponent, and a balanced playoff bracket was created with the point leaders from the season. During the normal season, teams were awarded two points for a map win, one point for a map tie, and zero points for a map loss. After many weeks of scheduling and round robin matches, our Counter-Strike: Global Offensive playoff teams have emerged.\r\n<h2>East Conference</h2>\r\nAfter the round robin normal season, four of our seven D2 teams have risen to the top of the East Conference. In order of playoff seed, our contenders are the Cincinnati Bearcats 3, Rutgers University – C, McGill Redmen D2, and New York University Div2A. Although these four teams ended up in the playoffs because the others in this conference went inactive during the normal season, they should not be taken for granted. With the Cincinnati Bearcats 3 being largely dominant in the last few months, New York University Div2A will have to put in some serious work to overtake their semifinal matchup. Rutgers University – C has also is a strong team in this conference, ending the season barely scoring lower than the top contender. The top two teams from this bracket will have an opportunity to play for the Division Two prize pool.\r\n<h2>West Conference</h2>\r\nAfter the round robin normal season, four of our seven D2 teams have also risen to the top of the West Conference. In order of playoff seed, our Western Conference playoff teams are Stanford University, Langara Association of Gaming Yellow, UC San Diego Division II Hype, and CrimsonAggie. Unlike the East Conference, all seven teams in the West Conference remained active for the entire normal season, so the teams at the top have seen more teams and play styles at the very least. At the top, Stanford University stands with almost twice as many points as its second place competition. The teams will have to work to overthrow the number one seed and earn a chance in the National Finals against the victor of the East Conference.\r\n<h2>Playoffs and Beyond</h2>\r\nIn the upcoming weeks, the teams will fight for the right to face their counterpart conference champion and win the Division Two championship title. As the matches play out and conference champions are crowned, be sure to check back <a href="http://www.ncespa.com/csgo/playoffs">here</a> to find updates. For the Counter-Strike: Global Offensive Division Two playoffs, the prize pool will have a total value of $450 in steam giftcards, with first place taking home $250, second taking $100, third and fourth taking $50 each. With half of the playoff teams earning a portion of the prize pool, the players will be in for some close matches!\r\n<h2>DIVISION ONE GRAND CHAMPIONSHIP</h2>\r\nIf you are keeping up with the Division Two playoff teams and championships, make sure you don’t miss out on the Division One Grand Championship as well. With the best teams in North America meeting in Santa Ana, California, stay tuned to the NCeSPA <a href="http://www.twitch.tv/ncespa">Twitch Channel</a> or grab tickets to the finals on June June 26th! The event will not only feature the finals for Counter-Strike: Global Offensive and League of Legends, but will also be a great place to meet fellow gamers, grab some free swag, and even witness our collegiate teams take on pro teams.', 'National Collegiate Counter-Strike League Season 2016 DII Regular Season Recap', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'nccsl-2016-d2-regular-season-recap', '', '', '2016-09-20 22:39:46', '2016-09-21 02:39:46', '', 0, 'http://esport.dev/?p=10', 0, 'post', '', 0),
