(31, 1, '2016-09-18 18:59:51', '2016-09-18 22:59:51', 'With the end of the regular season for both Counter-Strike: Global Offensive and League of Legends, playoff season has already begun, and the championship looms in the near future. As such, the National Collegiate eSports Association (NCeSPA) is proud to announce the following details for the 2016 National Collegiate eSports Association Grand Championship (NGC):\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>When</strong>: June 26th</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Where</strong>: eSports Arena | Santa Ana, California</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Event Page</strong>: <a href="http://www.ncespa.com/ngc">www.ncespa.com/ngc</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe matches played here will be the culmination of months of hard fought battles between the top collegiate eSports teams in North America. We will be inviting the top four collegiate teams from both the Counter-Strike: Global Offensive and League of Legends scenes to the eSports Arena in Orange County, California to compete for title of the best North American eSports teams in their respective games.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignleft wp-image-30 size-full" src="http://esport.dev/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ngc2016.png" alt="ngc2016" width="785" height="295" />\r\n<h2>What to Expect</h2>\r\nThe NGC is the largest event hosted by NCeSPA, happening once a year at the climax of the collegiate eSports season. After months of practice and close competition, the contestants are thirsty for the title of the best collegiate team in North America. And with a $20,000 prize pool, the largest NCeSPA has ever been able to offer, the stakes are high. The battles will be fierce, and the players unrelenting. Look forward to seeing new strategies, honed tactics, and flawless mechanics as the top players showcase what it means when the best of each region in an all out brawl on the center stage.\r\n<blockquote>“$20,000 prize pool, the largest NCeSPA has ever been able to offer”</blockquote>\r\n<h2>Saturday, June 25th</h2>\r\nThe semi-finals will be hosted on Saturday, June 25th. The matches will only be viewable live on our Twitch Channel. Coverage will start at 11:00AM pacific time and is expected to go until 10:00pm pacific time. Make sure to tune in as we determine who the top two teams from each featured game are. For both CS:GO and League of Legends, the top seed from the West will take on the top seed from the South, while the East and Midwest duke it out to produce our NGC finalists.\r\n\r\nIn parallel to our semi-finals, we are also hosting open tournaments for Smash 4, Melee, Project M, Street Fighter V, and Rocket League! If you are interested in participating in one of these events, head over to that announcement here!\r\n<h2>Sunday, June 26th</h2>\r\nOn Sunday June 26th, we are hosting the NGC Finals, open to live spectators at eSports Arena! Come support your fellow colleagues at 120 W 5th Street, Santa Ana, CA, 92701, as the top two teams in the nation battle it out for the title of Grand Champion in Counter-Strike: Global Offensive and League of Legends. Doors will open at 10:00am pacific time and the event is expected to go until 10:00pm pacific time. There will be sponsor booths, vendors, free swag, giveaways, raffles and not to mention tons of collegiate action! If you can’t make it, don’t worry, we will have stream-only giveaways as well, just make sure to tune in to our Twitch Channel during the event to see how to enter!\r\n<h2>How to Attend</h2>\r\nIf you are in the Santa Ana area or plan to travel out West for this event, be sure to check out our ticket prices here. It’s as simple as going online, buying a ticket, and showing up. Make sure to pick up tickets and book hotels early, as the event is sure to fill up quickly! Last year, our championship event drew in hundreds of attendees from the DC/Virginia/Maryland. Check out a recap of last year’s event and be sure to join us for the 2016 one! Also check out our Facebook event page and make sure to mark yourself as attending if you are!', 'National Collegiate eSports Association Announces Grand Championship Event', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '27-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-09-18 18:59:51', '2016-09-18 22:59:51', '', 27, 'http://esport.dev/news/27-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
